Appendix A: Detailed Proofs of Main Theorems

A.1 Proof of the Petz Recovery Condition (Theorem 3.3.2)

Theorem. Let $\mathcal{A},\mathcal{B}$ be finite‑dimensional C*-algebras, $\Phi:\mathcal{A}\to\mathcal{B}$ a UCP map, and $\omega$ a faithful state on $\mathcal{A}$. Set $\sigma=\Phi(\omega)$. The following are equivalent:

1. There exists a Bayesian inverse $\Phi^\dagger:\mathcal{B}\to\mathcal{A}$ (UCP) with $\Phi^\dagger(\sigma)=\omega$;
2. $D(\Phi(\rho)\|\Phi(\tau))=D(\rho\|\tau)$ for all states $\rho,\tau$ in the orbit of $\omega$;
3. $\sigma_t^\omega(\ker\Phi)\subseteq\ker\Phi$ for all $t\in\mathbb{R}$;
4. The Petz map $\mathcal{P}_{\omega,\Phi}$ satisfies $\Phi\circ\mathcal{P}_{\omega,\Phi}=\mathrm{id}_{\mathcal{B}}$ on the support of $\sigma$.

Proof. We prove (1)⇒(2)⇒(3)⇒(4)⇒(1).

(1)⇒(2). Assume $\Phi^\dagger$ exists with $\Phi^\dagger\circ\Phi=\mathrm{id}_{\mathcal{A}}$ and $\Phi^\dagger(\sigma)=\omega$. For any $\rho,\tau$ in the orbit of $\omega$, there exist $\rho',\tau'$ such that $\rho=\Phi^\dagger\circ\Phi(\rho')$, $\tau=\Phi^\dagger\circ\Phi(\tau')$. By monotonicity of relative entropy,
D(\rho\|\tau)=D(\Phi^\dagger\circ\Phi(\rho')\|\Phi^\dagger\circ\Phi(\tau'))\le D(\Phi(\rho')\|\Phi(\tau'))\le D(\rho'\|\tau')=D(\rho\|\tau).


Thus equality holds throughout, giving (2).

(2)⇒(3). Equality in the data processing inequality for all $\rho,\tau$ in the orbit of $\omega$ implies, by a theorem of Petz [1988], that there exists a conditional expectation $\mathbb{E}:\mathcal{A}\to\mathcal{A}^\Phi$ (the multiplicative domain of $\Phi$) preserving $\omega$ and satisfying $\mathbb{E}\circ\sigma_t^\omega=\sigma_t^\omega\circ\mathbb{E}$. Since $\ker\Phi$ is the orthogonal complement of $\mathcal{A}^\Phi$ in the GNS Hilbert space, invariance of $\mathcal{A}^\Phi$ under $\sigma_t^\omega$ implies invariance of $\ker\Phi$.

(3)⇒(4). Let $(H_\omega,\pi_\omega,\xi_\omega)$ be the GNS triple. Condition (3) implies that the projection $P$ onto $\overline{\pi_\omega(\mathcal{A}^\Phi)\xi_\omega}$ commutes with $\Delta_\omega^{it}$. Define the conditional expectation $\mathbb{E}(x)=PxP$ for $x\in\pi_\omega(\mathcal{A})''$. Then $\mathbb{E}$ is normal, faithful, and $\mathbb{E}\circ\sigma_t^\omega=\sigma_t^\omega\circ\mathbb{E}$. The Petz map is $\mathcal{P}_{\omega,\Phi}(b)=\pi_\omega^{-1}(\mathbb{E}(\pi_\sigma(b)))$ where $\pi_\sigma$ is the GNS representation of $\sigma$. By construction, $\Phi\circ\mathcal{P}_{\omega,\Phi}= \mathrm{id}_{\mathcal{B}}$ on the support of $\sigma$.

(4)⇒(1). The Petz map $\mathcal{P}_{\omega,\Phi}$ is UCP and satisfies $\Phi\circ\mathcal{P}_{\omega,\Phi}=\mathrm{id}_{\mathcal{B}}$ on the support of $\sigma$. Extend it arbitrarily outside the support to a UCP map $\Phi^\dagger$; then $\Phi^\dagger(\sigma)=\omega$ because $\mathcal{P}_{\omega,\Phi}(\sigma)=\omega$ by modular properties. ∎

