Appendix C: Essentials of Free Probability

C.1 Free Cumulants and $R$-Transform

Let $(\mathcal{M},\tau)$ be a tracial non‑commutative probability space. For a random variable $X$, the free cumulants $\kappa_n$ are defined by
\tau(X^n)=\sum_{\pi\in NC(n)}\prod_{V\in\pi}\kappa_{|V|}(X),


where $NC(n)$ is the set of non‑crossing partitions of $\{1,\dots,n\}$. The $R$-transform is $R_X(z)=\sum_{n\ge0}\kappa_{n+1}(X)z^n$. For freely independent $X,Y$, $R_{X+Y}(z)=R_X(z)+R_Y(z)$. The semicircular distribution has $R_S(z)=z$.

C.2 Free Fisher Information

The free difference quotient $\partial_X$ is defined on polynomials by
\partial_X(P(X))=\frac{P(X)-P(Y)}{X-Y}\Big|_{Y=X},


with the convention that the fraction is evaluated as a polynomial in $X$. The free Fisher information is $\Phi^*(X)=\|\partial_X\|_2^2=\tau((\partial_X)^*\partial_X)$. For freely independent $X_1,\dots,X_n$,
\Phi^*(X_1,\dots,X_n)=\sum_{i=1}^n\Phi^*(X_i).

C.3 Free Entropy

Voiculescu’s microstates free entropy of a self‑adjoint $X$ is
\chi(X)=\iint_{\mathbb{R}^2}\log|s-t|\,d\mu_X(s)\,d\mu_X(t)+\frac34,


where $\mu_X$ is the spectral distribution. The free log‑Sobolev inequality states: for a semicircular variable $S$,
\chi(\rho)\le\frac12\Phi^*(\rho)+ \text{constant}.

